  "text": "is processor symmetric (PS) if for every permutation λ : N Procs(P ) → N Procs(P ) we have σ ∈ traces(P ) implies λ proc (σ) ∈ traces(P ). A family is said to be location symmetric or processor symmetric if all protocols in its image have the respective property. Intuitively, data independence (DI) in a system means that variables of a certain type can only be nondeterministically assigned, copied, and outputted [CITATION_1] . When the system is a protocol, and the type is data values, one can define how DI manifests at the trace level. Qadeer [CITATION_2] gives the following trace level definition of DI. A trace is called unambiguous if it has the feature that no two writes to the same address write the same value. Given m, v, v ≥ 1, we call a function λ :",
